commitResults.messageBody:
# Changes
- There was a bug where the `edit` command was not being recommended for
auto complete, as it was always choosing the `edit_elderly` command
first. I modified the `findMatchingCommandInfo` method slightly:
- The method now accepts an additional argument `isExactMatching`. If
true, it will return the command with the exact matching to
`commandWord` (This is used when we know it's a "complete" command).
Otherwise, it will just perform a prefix matching as per normal.
- After filtering, we first sort the commands: This is so that shorter
and lexicographically smaller commands will get recommended first
- Modified the NRIC prefixes for the add commands to just use `nr\`
instead
- Modified the constraint message for `BirthDate` to better match the
regex given.
